Here's the research summary for Assignment 2, in plain language you can adapt:
________________________________________
1. AI Image Tool — Midjourney
•	What it does: Generates images from text prompts, producing highly detailed, artistic, and photorealistic visuals. Also supports image-to-video generation.
•	Pricing: Paid only — plans range from $10/month (Basic) to $120/month (Mega), with a 20% discount on annual billing. There is no free trial anymore. Tech Jacks Solutions
•	Strength: Produces some of the most visually striking and aesthetically refined images among AI generators, especially for artistic or conceptual work.
•	Limitation: Pricing is based on GPU processing time rather than a simple image count, which can make costs unpredictable, and there's no free tier to test it first.
2. AI Video Tool — Runway
•	What it does: Creates and edits videos using AI — including text-to-video, image-to-video, video inpainting, and green-screen removal. Popular with filmmakers and content creators for quick prototyping.
•	Pricing: Freemium — a limited free tier exists, with paid plans for more generation credits and higher-resolution output.
•	Strength: Very fast way to visualize ideas or storyboards without needing filming equipment or actors.
•	Limitation: Output length and consistency (e.g., character faces staying the same across frames) is still limited compared to traditional video production.
3. AI Coding Tool — GitHub Copilot
•	What it does: Acts as an AI pair-programmer inside code editors, suggesting code completions, writing functions, and explaining code through chat.
•	Pricing: Freemium — the free tier gives 2,000 code completions per month plus limited chat and agent access, while paid plans start at $10/month for individuals and $19/user/month for business teams. No Code MBA
•	Strength: Speeds up coding significantly by predicting and auto-completing code, reducing repetitive typing.
•	Limitation: Can produce code that looks correct but has subtle bugs or security issues, so it still requires human review.
4. AI Presentation Tool — Gamma
•	What it does: Automatically generates presentation slides (and documents/webpages) from a simple text prompt or outline, including layout, images, and design.
•	Pricing: Freemium — free plan with limited credits; paid plans unlock more generations and export options.
•	Strength: Saves a lot of time on formatting and design — you can go from an idea to a polished-looking deck in minutes.
•	Limitation: Design customization is more restrictive than tools like PowerPoint; complex or highly branded decks may need manual touch-up.
5. AI Website Builder — Framer AI
•	What it does: Generates a complete website (layout, content, and design) from a text description, which can then be edited visually without coding.
•	Pricing: Freemium — free plan for basic sites; paid plans needed for custom domains and advanced features.
•	Strength: Lets non-coders launch a professional-looking website very quickly.
•	Limitation: Complex functionality (e.g., custom backend logic, advanced integrations) still requires manual development or third-party tools.
6. AI Voice Tool — ElevenLabs
•	What it does: Converts text into realistic, natural-sounding speech in multiple voices and languages; also allows voice cloning.
•	Pricing: Freemium — free tier with limited monthly characters; paid plans scale up usage and unlock voice cloning.
•	Strength: Extremely realistic voice output, useful for narration, dubbing, and accessibility tools.
•	Limitation: Voice cloning raises ethical and misuse concerns (e.g., impersonation), and heavy usage gets expensive quickly on paid tiers.



